 {"id":"bd-aaiv","title":"Integrate cancellation injection with Lab and Oracles","description":"# Task

Integrate the cancellation injection framework with the existing Lab runtime
and Oracle system.

## Integration Points

1. **Lab::with_cancellation_injection()**: New builder method
   ```rust
   Lab::new()
       .with_cancellation_injection(InjectionStrategy::AllPoints)
       .with_oracle(TaskLeakOracle)
       .with_oracle(ObligationLeakOracle)
       .run(|cx| async { ... });
   ```

2. **Oracle Integration**: Run all oracles after each injection
   - Oracles already verify invariants
   - Need to collect oracle results per injection point
   - Report which invariants failed at which points

3. **Deterministic Execution**: Injection must be deterministic
   - Same seed + same injection point = same execution
   - Required for debugging failures

4. **Failure Isolation**: One injection failure shouldn't stop others
   - Continue testing other points
   - Collect all failures for report

## Oracle Checklist

The following oracles should run after each injection:

- [ ] TaskLeakOracle: No spawned task left unwaited
- [ ] ObligationLeakOracle: All permits/acks resolved  
- [ ] QuiescenceOracle: Region close = no live children
- [ ] LoserDrainOracle: Race losers fully drained
- [ ] CancellationProtocolOracle: Valid state transitions
- [ ] FinalizerOracle: Finalizers run exactly once

